name: Fatty Bom Bom x Nasi Kukus

reviews.text: Great tasting western food! Especially their chicken cutlet. Well fried, seasoned and generous portions for the price too. Service was prompt as well, considering they only had 1 person manning the stall at the time. Recommended!
Actually not the 1st time pasta not evenly cook, tdy I circled those which are hard n not cooked at all, disappointed.. (I picked some put on chilli pkt to show the dry n hard parts)
I had their nasi (rice) curry with üç≥ and crispy fried chicken sambal etc yum yum la ‚úÖ
Compared to when I have eaten it at the coffee shop, the portions are vastly different. Especially the chicken. Hope this doesn't happen again

UPDATE: Decided to give it a second chance and the staff was friendly! Maybe he was just having a bad day the first time I visited as he seems to be better rested and in a better mood. Shouldn't be faulted for that as we're all humans. Updated the rating :)

Previous entry: Indian (?) staff working was taking his own sweet time and even though I was standing at the counter waiting to order for 10mins, he totally ignored me despite him only dealing with only one plate of food. He only took my order once he finished with the order despite having plenty of time waiting and doing nothing and having no other customers. Food was okay I guess? Bought the Nasi Kari, would order again but would be mindful of these things if in a rush.
